<br>
I'll leave my musings out of it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthoricofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thoric of Brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Uber Gimp</span><br>  Posts: 656<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/1/01 2:05:34 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home1.gte.net/res007bh/BrianPic_copy.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Preserving the spirit of the server</span><hr size=1> /boggle. We spend a lot of time self congratulating ourselves about how wonderful our server is, but I don't see it. We have the same issues as every other server, and the same petty bs, we just cover it up in highfalutin language. And where other servers simply chose the might is right strategy we, by trying to be fair to everyone, decended into a dictatorship of the minority. One where a small minority of raiders use the rhetoric of democracy and fear of being slandered on the boards to propagate and continue a system which they consistantly abuse for their own benefit. <br>
<br>
I have to agree with Ganon, the spirit of this server, whatever it was, died out a long time ago at the hand of diminishing resources and increasing population. This courtesy that is constantly demanded of me has not been shown to me in ages. <br>
<br>
Let's look at reality. The system favors the small at the expense of the large. The large make up a majority of the raiding populace. Some of the large abuse the system by using smaller guilds and indys to whore for places in line. Some of the smaller guilds and indys abuse the system by allowing this to happen. A lot of people are unhappy with this setup, yet the people who abuse it call them the loot whores, and evil uberwhatevers out to abuse the system. Sorta ass backwards, ain't it. <br>
<br>
Guess what, our current system is unenforcable... yes completely unenforcable, and in fact anyone who tried to interfere with the raid of a guild who didnt follow our system would be warned or banned themselves, not the other way around...<br>
<br>
This means the only way a system will work is to get EVERYONE to buy into it. I said it when we instituted the original system and I'll say it now. If the system doesn't have fairness to everyone (large and small) there is no way it will fly, in the face of Verant's default FFA stance. <br>
<br>
Which means your alternatives are a system which the vast majority find fair, and will use peer pressure to enforce, or the default FFA. And in the default, a few large guilds will likely band together, form the classic uberguild, and we will be much as the other servers are. <br>
<br>
I'll likely be told im evil for even pointing this out, but that's silly. These are the bald facts of the matter. These are your realistic alternatives. I bring them to you not as a threat, but as a realistic assessment of our alternatives. You are free to decide what you think the best and worst alternatives are. <br>
<br>
